INSERT INTO `article` VALUES (1,'The Importance of Periodic Computer Maintenance','<p>Maintenance of your computer is essential to make your computer run efficiently.</p>','<p>Computers have an important role in human lives, it is the reason that it is significant that you take care of them. We use them every day for several purposes like for play games, paying bills, stream videos online, and much more. A good number of people require computers to carry out their professional work.</p><p>Maintenance of your computer is essential to make your computer run efficiently. A computer that is untreated can collect dust and debris, which may cause slower performance. In addition, if you do not update your antivirus, your computer can be infected with malware or virus. Computers work fine when you take care in a good way. You can buy the best computer money, but exclusive of usual PC maintenance, you can’t get the best bang for your buck.</p><p>Here are a few reasons why periodic computer maintenance is a good idea.</p><p><strong>Faster Computer</strong></p><p>Ultimately, the files that are stored on your PC may become unstructured and scattered, resulting in your PC taking more time to load and delays in accessing programs and files. We all dislike slow PCs, and with appropriate maintenance, you can make sure that your PC is functioning properly.</p><p>Our technicians are specialists in running speed and optimization checks, which can detect issues and keep your PC running at best speed.</p><p><strong>Expose Issues</strong></p><p>Whether you have a new computer or old, issues can pop up at any time. Computers are irregular, and we all know that small problems can become a big problem before we know it.</p><p>One of the important things about taking care of your computer is that you can identify any problem before it is too serious. When you do not maintain your PC well, it may be prone to problems that require attention. When you ignore problems, it can be dangerous for your computers.</p><p><strong>Avoid Viruses</strong></p><p>When your PC got infected, you may experience many symptoms ranging from irritating slowdown to popup messages.</p><p>When it comes to home or business, fixing it can be costly and can even cost the company in other ways, such as reduced productivity. But keeping your PC maintained in a good way can have both viruses and malware and help your computer run in tip-top shape. Periodic maintenance can also help you make sure that your antivirus program is the latest and working correctly.</p><p>If you keep your PC in good shape with periodic maintenance, it can enhance the life of your PC. When computers arrive at a certain point, they slow down, but sticking with care helps it run more powerfully.</p><p><strong>Speed up Your Computer</strong></p><p>There can be nothing more annoying than a computer that is slowly processing. But, as the majority of us can confirm too, with the passage of time our computers get clogged up with files and all get unsystematic and patchy.</p><p><strong>Maximize your Software Efficiency</strong></p><p>One more reason your PC may be slowing down over time is that your software package is becoming outdated. Since this change is gradual, your computer easily becomes accustomed to it and thinks it is normal.</p>','/public/img/articleImg/318f4b1b711d19809b5c190807f96d70','2020-04-21 16:00:00',1,'2020-06-11 07:09:35','2020-06-17 02:37:39',NULL,'/public/img/articleImg/fd1f34bc82ea73a8e17fbec822cac394'),(2,'The Difference between a Malware, Virus, and Spyware','<p>Most commonly viruses, malware, and spyware are those unwanted programs that damage your devices in different ways. Here we are going to explain the differences between viruses, malware, and spyware.</p>','<p>Most commonly viruses, malware, and spyware are those unwanted programs that damage your devices in different ways. Here we are going to explain the differences between viruses, malware, and spyware.</p><p><strong>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Malware</strong></p><p>Malware is a program that particularly harms the host system of the device. It can also consist of other kinds of software like worms, Trojan horses and spyware, etc. Highly developed malware like ransomware is used to commit financial scams and extort money from computer users. Malware is most damaging to mobile devices and PCs. There are different kinds of malware like viruses, adware, worms, and ransomware, etc.</p><p>In the present era, we can’t live without computer systems and mobile devices and we use them for a lot of purposes like communication, payments, and purchasing, etc. To get the protection of your devices and data against several types of malware is required. It is a reality that free antivirus programs are not much impressive as compared to paid antivirus programs.</p><p><strong>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Virus</strong></p><p>The virus itself is a particular kind of malware. It is a piece of infectious code that damages other programs on the host system and spreads itself on the go. Virus is generally familiar to spread when the program is shared between computer systems. It acts more similar to a parasite. Some viruses can harm your computer devices by removing the files, reformatting the hard drive and damaging other programs. Some of them simply duplicate themselves flood a network with traffic, making it not possible to make any internet activity.</p><p>All computer viruses are not destructive. However, most of them do things that are malicious like deleting data. Some viruses cause destruction as soon as their code is implemented. Some others remain unsafe until a particular event starts the program, causing their code to run in the device.</p><p>Viruses spread when the program or documents to which they are attached are transferred from one system to another via networks, disks, file sharing methods, etc. A number of viruses use dissimilar stealth policies to avoid identifying them with antivirus programs. T